%N A048860 Smallest denominator d such that the Sylvester expansion of n/d has n terms.
%H A048860 H. T. Freitag and G. M. Phillips, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-94-011-4271-7_16">Sylvester's algorithm and Fibonacci numbers</a>, in Applications of Fibonacci numbers, Vol. 8, 155-163, Springer, Dordrecht, 1999.
%F A048860 a(n) == 1 (mod n). - _Pontus von Brömssen_, Apr 25 2026
%e A048860 a(3) = 7 since 3/7 = 1/3 + 1/11 + 1/231
%o A048860 (PARI) a(n)=if(n==1,q=1,q=n+1;while(1,c=1;P=n;Q=q;while(Q%P>0,c++;D=Q\P+1;P=P*D-Q;Q*=D);if(c==n,break);q+=n));return(q)
